The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Lokuarachchi suspended 
Colombo: The Board of Control for Cricket in Sri Lanka (BCCSL) suspended Kaushal Lokuarachchi on Wednesday pending a disciplinary inquiry into his involvement in an accident that killed a woman and critically wounded her son, officials said. BCCSL decided to prevent him from taking part in all forms of the game until the completion of an internal investigation into his conduct, they said. (PTI)  Copyright 
